snippet.title: Shapes song for kids | The Singing Walrus
snippet.description:
Watch all of our videos ad free with our app (desktop, apple, or android):
https://www.thesingingwalrus.tv/
Only $4.99 USD per month and $44.99 USD for a year!

We are excited to present our Shape Song, a groovy and interactive song for kids that introduces four 2D shapes: circle, triangle, square, and rectangle. 

In each verse, a shape describes itself and asks the kids to guess what they are. As they introduce themselves, they turn into objects that resemble their shape, to show how they can be found in many different every day objects.

During the chorus, our cute characters ride a bus through a landscape in which they find lots of things made of the shapes they just learned about. The words and melody of the chorus are catchy and easy to sing along. We have also provided the lyrics on the screen for the teachers and parents!

Our Shape Song is great to use for home schooling or in the classroom as a part of a fun preschool activity. The illustrations inspire kids to draw shapes on their own, exploring each shape and their characteristics. 

If you like this video, don't forget to click the LIKE button :)
